Uses of Package
net.xqhs.util.logging

  • Classes in net.xqhs.util.logging used by net.xqhs.util.logging 
    Class Description
    BaseLogger
    This abstract class offers an implementation for the methods specified by the LoggerClassic interface, leaving only BaseLogger.l(net.xqhs.util.logging.Logger.Level, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object...) and BaseLogger.lr(java.lang.Object) to be implemented.
    Debug.DebugItem
    This interface must be implemented by all enumerations of debug constants in order to be able to use them as arguments of Logger.dbg(DebugItem, String, Object...) implementations.
    Debug.LogDebugItem
    The internal debug constants.
    Logger
    Any class that offers simple logging services (lf-li-lw-le-lr-dbg) to an external entity should implement this interface.
    Logger.Level
    Indicates the level of the log.
    LoggerClassic
    Any class that offers logging services to an external entity should implement this interface.
    LogWrapper
    Use this abstract class to implement any [wrapper of a] logging structure used in a Unit.
    LogWrapper.LoggerType
    Logger types included with this library.
    Unit
    The Unit class should be extended by classes in which logging primitives should be available without creating a specific object for logging.
    UnitComponent
    A class that extends Unit and exposes the logging and configuration methods.
    UnitLinkData
    A sub-configuration for linking the configured LogWrapper to another the "parent".
